				\begin{document}$${Q}_{gskd}={R}_{gs}\times {R}_{sk}\times {R}_{kd};\left(g\in G;s\in S;k\in K;d\in D\right)$$\end{document}g per unit of substrate s per unit of substrate (e.g., m3 of biogas per 1 t of cattle manure), Rsk is the output of substrate s per unit of resource k (e.g., t of cattle manure per 1 cattle) and Rkd is the size of resource k per district d (e.g., number of cattle in a certain district).

Total N, P2O5, or K2O potential of the region are calculated by the formula:
